comments: Caruso (LAL) places a marginal forearm to Rose (DET) and doesn't affect his SQBR.
Davis (LAL) sets the pick on Brown (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Drummond (DET) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
James (LAL) briefly places a marginal hand to Mykhailiuk's (DET) front before removing the contact at the start of the drive.
Howard (LAL) cleanly blocks Mykhailiuk's (DET) driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Wood (DET) makes marginal contact with Davis' (LAL) body during his driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with the ball while it is in the cylinder above the rim.
Brown (DET) and Davis (LAL) make incidental leg contact on the perimeter.
Drummond (DET) makes contact to Davis' (LAL) arm and affects his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Rose (DET) makes contact with the ball, but does not dislodge it before initiating lower leg contact with Caruso (LAL) that affects his SQBR.
Davis (LAL) makes marginal contact with Drummond's (DET) body during his shooting motion on the driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
